 {"id":"bd-32lt","title":"Semantic Events: Widget Migration Guide and Examples","description":"## Task

Create documentation and examples showing how to use semantic events in widgets.

## Documentation

Create `docs/semantic-events.md`:

1. Overview of semantic vs raw events
2. When to use which
3. Configuration options
4. Migration guide for existing widgets

## Example: List with Double-Click

```rust
enum Msg {
    // Raw events
    Key(KeyEvent),
    Mouse(MouseEvent),

    // Semantic events
    ItemClicked(usize),
    ItemDoubleClicked(usize),
    ItemDragged { from: usize, to: usize },
}

impl Message for Msg {
    fn from_semantic(event: SemanticEvent) -> Option<Self> {
        match event {
            SemanticEvent::DoubleClick { pos, .. } => {
                // Convert position to item index
                Some(Msg::ItemDoubleClicked(pos.y as usize))
            }
            SemanticEvent::DragEnd { start, end } => {
                Some(Msg::ItemDragged { 
                    from: start.y as usize, 
                    to: end.y as usize 
                })
            }
            _ => None
        }
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Comprehensive documentation
- [ ] Migration guide
- [ ] 3+ working examples
- [ ] Updated in demo showcase

## Alien Artifact Upgrades
- Model the core decision(s) with explicit state, priors/assumptions, and invariants; write down failure modes as first-class artifacts.
- Explainability: add an evidence ledger for any non-trivial decision (why this branch, why this fallback). Prefer Bayes factors / log-likelihood contributions over ad-hoc scoring.
- Guarantees: where prediction/thresholding exists, prefer distribution-free calibration (conformal prediction) or anytime-valid testing (e-process) so we can stop early without invalid inference.
- Graceful degradation: define capability tiers + deterministic fallbacks; never fail closed without a traceable reason.


## Extreme Optimization
- Baseline first: capture p50/p95/p99 for relevant command(s) with `hyperfine` (store raw output).
